Tips.
“Sorry, I forgot to tell you that someone called from the marketing department,” says a colleague.
Did you miss a meeting because of this?
At best, you regret it and try to make it up again, perhaps by calling the marketing department and confessing remorsefully that you have forgotten to direct the message (this is the less common method).
Most of the time, it’s done with an apology.
Before you get caught up in embarrassing excuses, you should think about what you can do to prepare your colleagues for really unpleasant moments and try to consciously avoid these situations.
Borrowing something that doesn’t belong to you?
There’s hardly anything more annoying than getting a document, office supplies, or the phone, but it’s not there.
Yesterday the sticker was still on the desk - this morning it's gone?
Or is the lost-believe ballpoint pen discovered on a colleague’s desk?
Without asking, one should not borrow anything from colleagues, because they are rightly annoyed when they find that something has gone away.
So, don’t put envelopes or post-it out of the office in your pocket, because it could hit yourself: no more there if you’re in urgent need.
Dealing with the private life of colleagues?
There is no effective way to stop a gossip that has already been put into the world.
Who did what with whom?
Where and why?
One should not tie the information (or assumptions) about the private life of colleagues to the nose of everyone if possible!
And if someone opens up and reveals his inner secret to us, we should not abuse this trust!
It is best to remain silent like a grave instead of aligning those who are not present, even if others are aware of the problems of the colleague.
Reported sick for no reason?
When you call the office to report sick on the grounds of annoying headaches, because you feel uncomfortable, or just want to rest, you should be aware of one thing: your own work, indisponible tasks, projects with fixed appointments must now be done by colleagues instead of one yourself.
Don’t play badly with your colleagues!
If you already know the day before that you will not be able to get into the office the next day, or that something could happen in between, why you need to stay at home, you should report it in time so that neither the colleagues nor the boss are unexpectedly confronted with the absence.
Total, Gekicher, Telephone
You are just getting deeper into your work, but are you suddenly disturbed by the loud chirping of your colleagues?
Did you hear a phone call that you shouldn’t have heard?
You should not annoy your colleagues with buzzing, singing, loud conversations (which you have over their heads), trampling, sneezing or snoring.
All this can be very disturbing, even if they are not deep into a task (writing, planning, organizing).
Is it always the other people’s fault?
If a project is not completed on time, you have forgotten to send an important letter or important messages, you should not look for the fault of your own forgetfulness in others!
If possible, you should not excuse yourself for the chaos in the office or the loud colleagues!
It is best to admit your mistakes and apologize if others were affected too!
The question of how to make up for the mistake, or the failure to recover, is just too appropriate!
In the office - a feeling at home?
Workout pants and sleeping: Comfortable for home, but has not lost anything in the office!
Not even then should you dress so casually if the workplace would actually allow it!
Just do not become too sloppy - you should respect both your colleagues and yourself to the extent that you dress appropriately in the office - if desired, also pretty and elegant!
