In parallel with the parliamentary preparation, which today ended its session with the resolution of Congress in the Senate on the additional/amendment proposals related to the project, the government published the provisions arising from the new law with the intention of enabling the entry into force of both regulations by the end of the year.
Representatives of the various companies unanimously commended the efforts of Congress and Senate MPs, who in their negotiations and votes had pursued the goal of establishing the best possible arrangement that ensures the safety of investors and regulates individual business activities in order to guarantee a generally efficient market development.
In addition to modernising the financial markets, the MIFID seeks to improve investor protection, increase the controlling power of the Spanish Securities Commission (CNMV) and promote cooperation between the various supervisory authorities of the European Union.
The new Directive allows for the provision of financial advisory services to both specialised firms and natural or legal persons, and also contributes to the creation of new financial services firms (ESIS), the advisory firms that combine with investment and securities brokerage companies.
In addition, it expands the number of systems for the execution of financial transactions, adding to the regulated circulating markets the multilateral securities trading systems and the systems for the internationalisation of trading orders, which would eventually enter into competition with the current economic actors.
The law obliges investment firms to notify the focus of their business profile, the confrontation and the forms of dealing with risks on the market and to register all the projects carried out in order to facilitate the CNMV’s task of control.
The Congressional Economic Commission foresaw further changes in the aftermath, with the decision that the bonds with titles now have to be considered complex financial assets due to their high level of risk to the investor, confirmed by the U.S. mortgage and banking crisis.
In addition, the entry into force of the Directive on the legal limitation of the fields of work of graduate economists was used; 30 years after 1977, the Regulation, which restricted the fields of work reserved for economists, was adopted.
The Senate, for its part, established new positions in the financial sector, such as that of the economic mediator, who works on a foreign account, does not require authorization from the CNMV and can offer its services for the commercialization of products and for customer acquisition at the same time to several investment companies.
