Which insurance is best for me?
The car insurance, which covers a possible accident caused by the driver, involves a high cost, the amount of which in turn depends on various factors, including age, gender, time of production of the driver’s license, family status, type of car to be insured and its use, etc.
Owning a car is just the beginning.
Because it is even more difficult to find the right car insurance than the right vehicle model.
First of all, we need to be clear about what we are dealing with here.
A car insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and an insurer.
This agreement is recorded in writing by means of an insurance contract which stipulates that the company receives the agreed insurance premium and in return is obliged to provide the corresponding amount of indemnity in case of damage.
The insurance premium is the price of an insurance that consists of several factors, including age, gender, time of issue of the driver's license, family status, type of vehicle to be insured or its use.
Insurance companies set their prices according to the statistics, so that in the event of a higher risk of accident, higher contributions are also due.
For this reason, both over 25-year-olds and women have to pay less contributions, because statistics prove that these groups have a lower accident rate thanks to their caution.
The same applies to married persons, since according to the statistical values and accordingly also according to the conviction of the companies, they tend to have fewer accidents than single people.
The benefit that is attributed to the vehicle affects the frequency of driving and thus also the likelihood of an accident.
The more frequent the use, the more likely the damage.
When setting up the premium, insurance companies must take into account a number of points.
For this reason, the driver must also thoroughly study the situation in order to select exactly the car insurance that most likely meets his personal needs.
At this point, we list the most important points to consider when choosing an insurance policy in order to be able to make not only a performance- but also a price-oriented choice.
Those under the age of 25 encounter numerous obstacles when choosing low-cost insurance, such as low driving experience and a young driver’s license.
Even if it would be best for an ideal insurance cover to take out full insurance, there are still cheaper alternatives.
Careful drivers can choose a full-casco with self-employment, so that while the benefits of full-casco insurance are covered, they are offered at a low price.
This type of contract implies that the customer has to pay part of the amount incurred by the damage itself.
The amount is set before the conclusion of the contract and based on the amount of the insurance premium, which is higher the lower the amount to be paid , explains Luis Noguera, Spain’s chief representative at First Europa, an online insurance brokerage company.
Another option is extended insurance, which insures the customer against external accident damage, but not against the damages caused on his own car.
In addition, this type of insurance would cover theft, fire and vehicle loss.
Here's some advice.
If you’re under 25, it’s up to you to lower your insurance costs, so your credit increases by trying to drive cautiously and avoid accidents.
A credit is a reduction in the basic rate of the respective insurance company.
On the contrary, a penalty payment involves an increase in said rates.
The amount of credits and penalties depends on the company and its profits.
If the company has a profitable year behind it, it can afford to increase the bonus payments, Noguera explains.
Once the 25-year mark is exceeded, it is easier for drivers to conclude a contract, due to the fact that with increasing driving practice, the accident rate decreases.
Therefore, it is most sensible to opt for full insurance with self-employment.
Normally, young people cannot benefit from their previous experience, both in the event of an accident and at the time of driving, explains the Spanish head of the European company, adding that the majority of accidents occur in the second year of practice after the fear of the beginner has been relieved.
However, in the case of a married client who does not have children, it is more advisable to take out full-case insurance; of course, only if the financial situation of the corresponding person also allows it.
Insurers consider married couples with children to be the customers with the lowest accident rate, and consequently, their contribution payments are also low.
In this case, full-case insurance with self-employment (with an amount of around 300 euros) would be the best option. In case you have received a high credit, an extended insurance is recommended, which is only used for the third year of the vehicle.
They drive more relaxed overall and have a greater purchasing power that allows them to make a higher contribution payment, notes Luis Noguera.
For pensioners, it is a good idea to take out full insurance with self-employment (at an amount of 150 euros), or an extended insurance, which is only used with a sufficient amount of credit.
Ultimately, it must be noted that car insurance is something very important, not only because it protects the driver from possible accident damage, but also because it carries high costs that require that a thorough selection be made that corresponds to our personal situation.
