The trade fair seemed to be primarily aimed at the new rich, the type of brand-conscious Russian buyers who would be willing to stand for several hours in the traffic jam to visit a congested warehouse that tastelessly designs Cadillac Escalades, pocket knives made of platinum, Mövenpick ice cream, and bespoke ice cream.
