In the Philippines, rebel soldiers have surrendered who hid in a hotel in Manila and demanded the overthrow of President Gloria Macapagal Arroyo.
He could not be responsible for bloodshed, leader Antonio Trillanes, who accused the president of corruption and electoral fraud, told reporters at the hotel.
Government-loyal soldiers had previously stormed the hotel under tear gas.
The about two dozen soldiers had been entangled in the building for hours.
About half of them were in court on Thursday for a failed coup attempt in 2003, among them Trillanes.
He took advantage of the negotiation to suddenly settle down with about 30 sympathizers.
The military policemen, who were supposed to guard him, apparently overtook him and joined his mutiny.
